25|$|The Society of Actuaries (SOA) is a {{professional}} organization for actuaries based in North America. It was founded in 1949 as the merger of two major actuarial organizations in the United States: the Actuarial Society of America and the American <b>Institute</b> <b>of</b> <b>Actuaries.</b> It is a full member organization of the International Actuarial Association.|$|E
